The paper deals with a mathematical model of real-world networks, specifically the multiplicative attribute graph (MAG) model, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses methods from graph theory and probability theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The study of the connectivity and degree distribution of the MAG model is also related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses the method of moments, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT).
